Aim:
To write a C++ function template that works for multiple data types.

Algorithm:
Start program.
Create a function template using template <class T>.
Write a generic function (e.g., add two values).
Call the function with different data types.
Display results.
End program.

Program:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

template <class T>
T add(T a, T b) {
    return a + b;
}

int main() {
    cout << "Integer Add: " << add(10, 20) << endl;
    cout << "Float Add: " << add(5.5, 2.3) << endl;
    return 0;
}

Output:
Integer Add: 30
Float Add: 7.8

Result:
Function templates were successfully implemented for multiple data types.

